cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use evalkit in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "evalkit: Rigorous LLM Evaluation"
abstract: >
  evalkit is a Python library for statistically rigorous evaluation of large
  language models. It provides bootstrap confidence intervals on every metric,
  McNemar's test and Wilcoxon signed-rank test for model comparison,
  Benjamini-Hochberg FDR correction for multiple prompt variants, power
  analysis before running experiments, and an automated RigorChecker audit
  that flags underpowered experiments, class imbalance, and unreliable judges.
authors:
  - family-names: "McConnell"
    given-names: "Bonnie"
version: 0.2.0
date-released: "2026-04-25"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/bonnie-mcconnell/evalkit"
keywords:
  - llm-evaluation
  - statistical-testing
  - bootstrap
  - nlp
  - machine-learning
